prefer-spread.description:
Description

This rule is aimed to flag usage ofFunction.prototype.apply()in situations where spread syntax could be used instead.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint prefer-spread: "error"*/

foo.apply(undefined, args);
foo.apply(null, args);
obj.foo.apply(obj, args);

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint prefer-spread: "error"*/

// Using spread syntax
foo(...args);
obj.foo(...args);

// The `this` binding is different.
foo.apply(obj, args);
obj.foo.apply(null, args);
obj.foo.apply(otherObj, args);

// The argument list is not variadic.
// Those are warned by the `no-useless-call` rule.
foo.apply(undefined, [1, 2, 3]);
foo.apply(null, [1, 2, 3]);
obj.foo.apply(obj, [1, 2, 3]);
